cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the privacy risks associated with machine learning algorithms, specifically in terms of overfitting and influence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves empirical analyses and formal analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of popular machine learning algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions model inversion attacks, which could also place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
